## 10. Security Best Practices

### Smart Contract Security
- [ ] ReentrancyGuard on all transfers
- [ ] Use SafeERC20 or safe transfer patterns
- [ ] OpenZeppelin Ownable for admin functions
- [ ] Before mainnet: Get formal audit (e.g., Certik, Trail of Bits)
- [ ] Test all edge cases (zero amounts, large numbers, etc.)

### Backend Security
- [ ] Rate limiting on API endpoints
- [ ] Input validation (check wallet addresses, amounts)
- [ ] HTTPS only (SSL/TLS)
- [ ] JWT tokens with short expiry (15 mins)
- [ ] Refresh tokens stored in httpOnly cookies
- [ ] CORS whitelist (only your frontend domain)
- [ ] Environment variables never committed to git

### Frontend Security
- [ ] Never store private keys in frontend
- [ ] Never hardcode secrets
- [ ] Use Content Security Policy headers
- [ ] Regular dependency updates (`npm audit`)
- [ ] Wallet address validation before sending txs

### Crypto Best Practices
- [ ] Use Alchemy API (better rate limits than free RPC)
- [ ] Multi-sig for treasury (Gnosis Safe)
- [ ] Insurance for smart contracts (optional)

